a pink themed website that shares info about the following person and gives space for their portfolio. the ui should be modern and rounded corners on everything. info about the person:MICHELLE LAWSON Smith College - Northampton MA, USA, Graduating May 2026. Major: Computer Science, GPA 3.84. Relevant Coursework: Algorithms, Data Structures, Object Oriented Programming, Theory of Computation, Financial Statement Modeling. Technical Skills: Python, Java, R, Excel, Quantitative Analysis, Statistical Programming. Soft Skills: Analytical Thinking, Communication, Leadership, Planning. Computer Science Research - Northampton, MA, May 2023 - August 2023. Undergraduate Research Fellow. Spearheaded statistical analysis, management, curation, and interpretation of large datasets on 200 students’ performance and backgrounds to drive research direction. Utilized R and Python to analyze and visualize data, contributing significantly to the understanding and presentation of research statistics. Presented data-driven recommendations to the research team to optimize educational strategies in computer science, demonstrating the application of quantitative analysis in decision-making. Smith College - Northampton, MA, Oct 2022 - Present. Student Affairs Intern. Facilitated communication between 2,900 students, families, and staff. Managed the planning and execution of 2 student orientation events with 700 attendees. Schoolhouse.world - Remote, July 2021 - Oct 2021. Volunteer Tutor & Community Engagement Team Member. Tutored 74 learners from 21 countries in Computer Science, Mathematics & Spanish. Adapted to 41 student needs by planning and executing individualized tutoring sessions tailored to specific student needs and feedback. Educating Computer Science Girlies: Successfully built and led a thriving online community, Computer Science Girlies, with over 50,000 TikTok followers and 2,000 members on Discord. Leveraged effective communication and leadership skills to educate and connect